02/07/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Kicking off a three-day visit on Tuesday (1 July), Turkish President Ahmet Necdet Sezer said his country is committed to helping Macedonia join NATO and the EU. Sezer and his Macedonian counterpart, Boris Trajkovski, also discussed ways of promoting better economic ties, as well as the Pan-European Transport Corridor 8 and other regional issues. Sezer is scheduled to meet with Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski, Parliament Speaker Nikola Popovski and representatives of the Turkish minority in Macedonia.
In other news, Macedonia and Albania agreed Tuesday to sign an accord later this month protecting Lake Ohrid. It is already protected by UNESCO for its natural and cultural heritage. (AFP, MIA, A1 TV - 01/07/03)
